      "acceptanceCriteria": "SQA procedures documented; version control and regression testing in place for solver used in hemolysis prediction.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2021R2) is deployed under a documented SQA plan including version-controlled input files, automated regression testing against canonical benchmark cases, and change-control procedures. All SQA records are archived in the project repository. Gradation 2 requirements are fully satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy test using manufactured solution confirms solver convergence behavior consistent with stated discretization scheme.",
      "rationale": "A method of manufactured solutions (MMS) test was executed on the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver. Observed spatial order of accuracy was 1.97 ± 0.04, consistent with the second-order finite-volume scheme. Temporal convergence confirmed at first order for the pseudo-transient formulation. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 5% on primary QoI (hemolysis index) using at least three mesh refinement levels.",
      "rationale": "Three structured hexahedral meshes (2.1M, 6.8M, 18.4M elements) were evaluated. Richardson extrapolation yielded GCI = 1.7% on the hemolysis index at the worst-case operating point (3 L/min, 3500 RPM). All five operating conditions exhibited GCI < 2.5%. Achieves Gradation 3 due to systematic three-level convergence study with quantified uncertainty bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
