      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental data were collected at five flow-speed operating points spanning the CPB clinical range. Test fluid (glycerol-water analog) viscosity and density are documented; boundary conditions in the CFD model match within 1.2% for flow rate and 0.5% for rotational speed. Temperature variation during testing was ±0.3°C, within the acceptable range. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulated hemolysis index (RH) compared against experimental measurements; agreement within 15% at all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Simulated normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) were compared against FDA benchmark experimental measurements at all five operating conditions. Maximum deviation was 7.8% (at 5 L/min, 2500 RPM); mean absolute error was 4.3%. RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all points relative to predicate device. Gradation 2 requirements met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
