      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH), which directly maps to the RH < 1 clinical acceptance criterion. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, exposure time) support mechanistic understanding. All QoIs are standard metrics for blood pump hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
