      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters (geometry, boundary conditions, fluid properties) are demonstrated to be equivalent to experimental conditions used in validation.",
      "rationale": "A comprehensive qualitative assessment of input parameter equivalency was performed by the credibility assessment team. Geometric fidelity was confirmed through direct comparison of CAD model dimensions against the FDA reference geometry specification, with all critical clearances and blade angles verified within manufacturing tolerances. Fluid property equivalency was established through review of the glycerol-water mixture characterization data, confirming viscosity and density match within the bounds established by prior hemolysis surrogate validation studies in the literature. Rotational speed and volumetric flow rate boundary conditions were mapped directly from experimental test records to simulation inputs, with documented traceability. The assessment team concluded that the degree of input parameter equivalency is sufficient to support the validation comparison and the COU acceptance decision. This qualitative evaluation, drawing on subject matter expertise and documented engineering judgment, provides adequate confidence in parameter equivalency for the MRL 2 classification of this device."
